                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–1049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Major
                        General <persName type="to">Patrick J. Hurley</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="77" xml:id="d503fn77">Transmitted through military channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-17">November 17,
                            1944</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 121. If agreeable, would like to appoint you as Ambassador to China. Your
                    intimate knowledge of the situation there, both from the military and diplomatic
                    standpoints, I feel eminently qualifies you for this important post during the
                    present critical times.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
